'''ISO 3166-2:LK''' code for the [[Sri_Lanka#Provinces and districts|subdivisions of Sri Lanka]]. The purpose of this family of standards is to establish a worldwide series of short abbreviations for places, for use on package labels, containers and such. Anywhere where a short alphanumeric code can serve to clearly indicate a location in a more convenient and less ambiguous form than the full place name. 

